          "author": {
            "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
          },
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\nReport: `docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\nFinding: #34\n\nMoved from mistakenly filed meta issue: ConcaveTrillion/ocr-container-meta#327\n\nEvidence:\n\n- `pd_book_tools/licenses.py:15`\n- `pd_book_tools/data/spdx_licenses.json:1`\n- `LICENSE:1`\n\nThe module says SPDX data is vendored from `license-list-data`, but the data file begins directly with data and the repository license only covers the project.\n\nImpact:\n\n- Redistributors may not know the license/source/version of the vendored data.\n\nRemediation:\n\n- Add a third-party notice or adjacent metadata naming SPDX source, version/date, and license.\n\n---\nThis issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
          "closedAt": "2026-05-22T16:34:42Z",
